so you gotta think about likee how fast your generationh is right
say 4 seconds
you have 120 volume in 10 minutes
120 / 10 = 12 a minute = need to be doing a generation every 5 seconds for each miner so that volume is fine for 4 second generation
so heres where max concurrent comes in, if you have say really high volume, you're often going to need to have like a "queue" of items.
so you take your generation time of 4 seconds

concurrency isnt really concurrency if every gpu is occupied so it ends up being more like a little queue for each miner so timeout/generation time is a fine number for max concurrent
